content:
The `FileTree` component renders a hierarchical tree structure of files and folders, commonly used for navigating a project's file system or documentation structure. It supports expanding and collapsing folders, selecting files, and indicating the active file or folder.

## Key Exports/Functions/Props:

*   **`FileTree` Component:**
    *   **`nodes`**: An array of `TreeNode` objects representing the files and folders to display.
    *   **`activeKey`**: The key of the currently selected file.
    *   **`activeFolderPath`**: The path of the currently active folder.
    *   **`onSelect`**: A callback function triggered when a file is selected. It receives the file's `key`.
    *   **`onFolder`**: A callback function triggered when a folder is clicked to navigate to its content. It receives the folder's `path`.
    *   **`depth`** (optional): The current nesting level of the tree (used for recursive rendering).
    *   **`pathPrefix`** (optional): A prefix to prepend to folder paths for generating unique identifiers.

*   **`FolderRow` Component (Internal):**
    *   Renders a single folder in the tree.
    *   Manages its own `open` state for expanding/collapsing.
    *   Displays a chevron icon for toggling visibility.
    *   Navigates to the folder's page when the folder name is clicked.

*   **`FileRow` Component (Internal):**
    *   Renders a single file in the tree.
    *   Highlights the row if it's the `activeKey`.
    *   Triggers the `onSelect` callback when clicked.

*   **`FolderIcon` Component (Internal):**
    *   Renders an icon for a folder, changing appearance based on its `open` state.

*   **`FileIcon` Component (Internal):**
    *   Renders a generic icon for a file.

## Usage Example:

```typescript
import React from 'react';
import { FileTree } from './FileTree';
import type { TreeNode } from './lib/tree'; // Assuming TreeNode definitions are in './lib/tree'

const sampleNodes: TreeNode[] = [
  {
    kind: 'folder',
    name: 'src',
    children: [
      { kind: 'file', name: 'index.tsx', key: 'src/index.tsx', title: 'Main entry point' },
      {
        kind: 'folder',
        name: 'components',
        children: [
          { kind: 'file', name: 'Button.tsx', key: 'src/components/Button.tsx', title: 'Reusable button' },
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  { kind: 'file', name: 'README.md', key: 'README.md', title: 'Project documentation' }
];

function App() {
  const [activeKey, setActiveKey] = React.useState<string | null>('src/index.tsx');
  const [activeFolderPath, setActiveFolderPath] = React.useState<string | null>(null);

  const handleSelectFile = (key: string) => {
    setActiveKey(key);
    setActiveFolderPath(null); // Deselect active folder when a file is selected
  };

  const handleSelectFolder = (path: string) => {
    setActiveFolderPath(path);
    setActiveKey(null); // Deselect active file when a folder is selected
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Project Files</h2>
      <FileTree
        nodes={sampleNodes}
        activeKey={activeKey}
        activeFolderPath={activeFolderPath}
        onSelect={handleSelectFile}
        onFolder={handleSelectFolder}
      />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```
